\f2\b0\fs22 \cf0 \ul \ulc0 Macro usage notes:\
\
\ulnone -  All fields are displayed in the preview and editor as expanded values (if the string is defined).\
-  Use cmd-R in the editor to edit the "raw" BibTeX directly; this is what the value will look like when saved to disk.\
-  If you delete the outer braces in the raw editor, they will not appear when saved.  For example, to enter an abbreviated month, select the "Month" field, hit cmd-R (or use the menu item), delete the braces that appear, and enter the abbreviated month.  The expanded value will also be shown.\
-  To edit @string definitions, use the "Window->Macros" menu item (cmd-shift-m); there is a separate macro editor for each document, and you can drag existing @string definitions directly into the macro editor table.
\f4\b \

\f2\b0 \
\ul Taking Care of your Data:\
\ulnone \
We recommend keeping important information in a version control system such as CVS.\
Also remember that if you just open a file, and don't save it as the same name - you 
\f4\b can't 
\f2\b0 kill the original file.\
\
\ul When it may cause you to lose data if you save over a file:\
\
\ulnone - If your database doesn't parse completely and you choose to only use the ones that did, you will lose any information in the ill-formed entries!  If you choose to open the file and save it from BibDesk, save it with an alternate name so you don't overwrite the old file.
\f4\b \

